works.description: Last year, we saw some record-breaking auctions, including the 78-year-old Pablo Picasso painting “Nude, Green Leaves and Bust” that fetched a whopping $106.5 million, thereby breaking the previous world record for any work of art sold at auction. Now, an anonymous donor from America has given the University of Sydney a rare Picasso painting to raise money for scientific research. The1935 painting, called Jeune fille endormie, shows Picasso’s mistress and frequent subject, Marie-Therese Walter.
